critical_positive: I think what really worked well is that my conversation partner's job is basically my dream job, so for me I asked him a lot about it and listened to him talk about art. critical_negative: I have to imagine that my responses weren't anywhere near as interesting for him, although I really tried my best. As well, I wonder if it was maybe a little boring for him to basically just talk about the same things he talks about every single day, but I'm not sure.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning there were some pleasantries about one another, then we chatted about our locations a bit. Oh and breakfast.
middle_memory_text: We began talking about art. This was a great topic for both of us. She and I both have an interest in the arts, so we chatted about the artists we like and about working and studying the arts.
end_memory_text: We chatted more about the artists we like, and the philosophy of arts. I feel like I spent a lot of time talking during this portion, but she seemed interested.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week as fairly busy. I have to move house this weekend. I am going to rent a truck and move furniture tomorrow. During the rest of the week, I will be very busy at work doing a lot of physical activity. I am looking forward to it.
critical_positive: I think what worked best about the conversation I just had was a shared interest in the arts. She and I both went to art school, and have an interest in art in general. This was the best part of the conversation. I think we could have talked about that topic for a while.
critical_negative: I think what didn't work well in the conversation was that it was a sort of forced interaction with someone you don't know, so getting to know someone from nothing, no cues or anything, can be a struggle to find similar interests. My partner hadn't done any of these chats before, she seemed a bit shy and reserved, but still interested.
